                 <h2></h2> <!--- my story -->
               </div>
               <div class="centerme"> <!-- originally col-md-9 -->
                  <p>
                     During my internship at Apple, I explored the intersection of operations and film, specifically from a learning and development standpoint.
                  </p>
                  <p> 
                     I created video training content for members of the iPhone, iPad, Mac & Apple Watch supply and demand management teams. Eager to have global impact, I collaborated with the VP of Worldwide Operations to produce a series of Apple culture and values videos that will be used for onboarding in the entire operations organization. 
                  </p>
                  <p>
                     So that the global learning and development teams were well equipped to produce videos independently, I designed a comprehensive video production training modules. Given interest from other teams within operations, this training module can be rolled out to other functions within Apple. Throughout the summer, I presented my internship project progress to operations teams in Cupertino, Singapore and Cork.
                  </p>
